    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Season your<strong> beef mince</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Massage the meat with clean hands for 1 min (this helps them to hold their shape whilst cooking)</p><p>Divide the mince and shape them into 1 <strong>patty</strong> per person</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1624268430489-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1624268430489-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1624268430489-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1624268430489-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1624268430489-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the fries have been in for 15-20 min, heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>beef patty[ies]</strong>, press down firmly with a spatula and cook for 5 min</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 5? You may need to do this in batches!</p><p>Flip the <strong>patty[ies]</strong> and reduce the heat to medium-high and cook for 3 min further</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1624268434144-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1624268434144-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1624268434144-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1624268434144-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1624268434144-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the patty[ies] are cooking, cut your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half and spread them with the<strong> garlic & herb butter</strong></p><p>Add to a baking tray (or two!), butter-side up, and put the tray[s] in the oven for 3-4 min or until golden – this is your <strong>garlic & herb brioche bun[s]</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1624268438969-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1624268438969-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1624268438969-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1624268438969-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1624268438969-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, flip the beef patty[ies] and top with the <strong>grated cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Cover loosely with a lid (or some tin foil!) and cook for 2-3 min further or until the cheese has melted and the patty[ies] are cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Meanwhile, wash your<strong> gem lettuce </strong>and set the <strong>leaves</strong> aside for serving</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1624268443024-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1624268443024-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1624268443024-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1624268443024-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1624268443024-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Spread the base of the<strong> garlic & herb brioche bun</strong> with some <strong>truffle & black pepper mayo</strong></p><p>Build your burger by topping the<strong> base </strong>with some <strong>lettuce leaves</strong>,<strong> </strong>a<strong> cheesy patty </strong>and<strong> </strong>some more <strong>truffle & black pepper mayo</strong> then top with the<strong> lid</strong></p><p>Serve with the <strong>smoky sweet potato fries</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
